The '''Malabar imperial pigeon''' or '''Nilgiri imperial pigeon''' ('''''Ducula cuprea''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Columbidae]]. It is [[endemic]] to the [[Western Ghats]] of [[India]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Malabar Imperial-Pigeon - eBird |url=https://ebird.org/species/mouimp1 |access-date=2023-02-11 |website=ebird.org |language=en}}</ref>

Its natural [[habitat]]s are subtropical or tropical moist lowland [[forest]]s and subtropical or tropical moist [[montane forest]]s. It previously was considered a subspecies of the [[mountain imperial pigeon]], but was split due to differences in morphology and plumage. This split was later supported by an analysis of its [[Bird vocalization|calls]].<ref name="Niranjana">{{cite journal |last1=Niranjana |first1=C |last2=Praveen |first2=J |title=Vocalisation of Mountain Imperial Pigeon ''Ducula badia'' and its taxonomic implications |journal=Indian Birds |date=2021 |volume=17 |issue=3 |pages=70-72 |url=https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Praveen-Jayadevan/publication/353314587_Vocalisation_of_Mountain_Imperial_Pigeon_Ducula_badia_and_its_taxonomic_implications/links/60f2eca49541032c6d49b1ac/Vocalisation-of-Mountain-Imperial-Pigeon-Ducula-badia-and-its-taxonomic-implications.pdf |access-date=20 September 2024}}</ref>

